com.hazelcast.internal.networking.nio

Class NioInboundPipeline

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.internal.networking.nio.NioPipeline
      • com.hazelcast.internal.networking.nio.NioInboundPipeline
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MigratablePipeline, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public final class NioInboundPipeline
extends NioPipeline
    When the NioThread receives a read event from the Selector, then the process() is called to read out the data from the socket into a bytebuffer and hand it over to the ChannelInboundHandler to get processed.

      • requestMigration

        public void requestMigration(NioThread newOwner)
        Migrates this Pipeline to a new NioThread. The migration logic is rather simple:

        • Submit a de-registration task to a current NioThread
        • The de-registration task submits a registration task to the new NioThread

        Parameters:
        newOwner - target NioThread this pipeline migrates to

      • process

        public void process()
             throws Exception
        Description copied from class: NioPipeline
        Called when there are bytes available for reading, or space available to write. Any exception that leads to a termination of the connection like an IOException should not be handled in the handle method but should be propagated. The reason behind this is that the handle logic already is complicated enough and by pulling it out the flow will be easier to understand.
        Specified by:
        process in class NioPipeline
        Throws:
        Exception
